quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,109,"And they swear their strongest oaths by Allâh, that if there came to them a sign, they would surely believe therein. Say: "
  6,110,"And We shall turn their hearts and their eyes away (from guidance), as they refused to believe therein for the first time, and We shall leave them in their trespass to wander blindly."
  6,111,"And even if We had sent down unto them angels, and the dead had spoken unto them, and We had gathered together all things before their very eyes, they would not have believed, unless Allâh willed, but most of them behave ignorantly."
  7,19,""
  7,20,"Then Shaitân (Satan) whispered suggestions to them both in order to uncover that which was hidden from them of their private parts (before); he said: "
  7,21,"And he [Shaitân (Satan)] swore by Allâh to them both (saying): "